  "explanation": "The Big Bang theory describes how the universe began from a tiny, extremely dense point called a singularity. This event happened billions of years ago and caused everything to expand rapidly. Since then, cosmic expansion has continued, making space larger and galaxies moving apart. Scientists believe all matter and energy emerged from this initial explosion. The universe was once very hot and small, then cooled down over time. Today, we see evidence like the cosmic microwave background radiation supporting this view. It explains why the universe looks the way it does now. This model helps us understand the origin of stars, planets, and life itself. We still study these ancient events to learn more about reality.",
